modules.description: This module defines the default configuration parameters for identifier generation, including the character set, minimum length, and blocked strings. It provides direct access to the default alphabet, minimum length value, and blocklist entries. These values are used to initialize and customize identifier encoding and decoding processes.

This module generates and decodes short, unique string identifiers from integer sequences. It supports customizable alphabets, minimum output lengths, and blocklists to control the generated strings. Concrete use cases include shortening URLs, obfuscating numeric IDs in APIs, and generating user-facing tokens that avoid ambiguous or inappropriate words.
